      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve reverted the requestEncoded guard you suggested here, in favour of JY-Voon\u0027s approach in the sibling comments — the request is now a const member initialized in the constructor initializer list.\n\nReasoning: encode*Request() only returns non-zero when the output buffer is smaller than the packed bytes, but the buffer is a constexpr-sized std::array that matches the request size, so encode cannot fail at runtime. A size/encoder drift would be a build-time bug, not a runtime condition, so the guard was protecting a path that can\u0027t be hit in practice.\n\nIf you\u0027d still prefer a guard, could you and JY-Voon settle on a direction here? Happy to go either way once you two align.",
